## remove dual boot

<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7GRUsnVNLNg>

## Pop OS

### installation

### Grub
**remember to create an temp boot partition instead of using the old and fuck windows boot entry**
sudo apt install grub-efi grub2-common grub-customizer
sudo grub-install
sudo cp /boot/grub/x86_64-efi/grub.efi /boot/efi/EFI/pop/grubx64.efi
-> open grub-customizer

### initial
install [swapfile 8 gb](https://linuxize.com/post/how-to-add-swap-space-on-ubuntu-20-04/)


